annotationA: Aminolevulinate synthase is a mitochondrial enzyme involved in cuticle barrier formation and thought to have a role in Heme biosynthesis; Belongs to the class-II pyridoxal-phosphate-dependent aminotransferase family
annotationB: Delta-aminolevulinic acid dehydratase; Porphobilinogen synthase activity; metal ion binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process; Belongs to the ALAD family
